</div> 
<p><strong>Gelmir Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Staff" href="/Glintstone+Staff">Glintstone Staff</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Gelmir Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith">Faith</a>, with minor scaling in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>, and&nbsp;is a good&nbsp;hybrid Intelligence/Faith&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for casting <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magma Sorceries" href="/Magma+Sorceries">Magma sorceries</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Staff with a forked tip, embedded with red glintstones. Enhances lava sorceries.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>The Man-Serpents of Mt. Gelmir draw from faith in addition to intelligence to enhance the potency of their sorcery.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Gelmir Glintstone Staff</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>The <strong>Gelmir Glintstone Staff</strong> is an uncommon drop from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Man-Serpent Sorcerer" href="/Man-Serpent+Sorcerer">Man-Serpent Sorcerer</a>&nbsp;in the throne room above <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Volcano Manor" href="/Volcano+Manor">Volcano Manor</a>.</li> 
 <li>It is recommended that players use a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Silver-Pickled Fowl Foot" href="/Silver-Pickled+Fowl+Foot">Silver-Pickled Fowl Foot</a> for each run up to the throne room to boost item discovery from killing enemies as well as unlock the lift leading from the <strong>Temple of Eiglay</strong> Site of Grace to the throne room. Due to the&nbsp;relatively low drop rate, it may take multiple runs and teleports back to the site of grace to see the staff drop.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Gelmir Glintstone Staff Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: No skill</li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li>Cannot enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic">Magic</a>&nbsp;or buffed by&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Gelmir Glintstone Staff</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Magma&nbsp;sorceries include <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gelmir's Fury" href="/Gelmir's+Fury">Gelmir's Fury</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magma Shot" href="/Magma+Shot">Magma Shot</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roiling Magma" href="/Roiling+Magma">Roiling Magma</a>, and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard's Rancor" href="/Rykard's+Rancor">Rykard's Rancor</a>.</li> 
 <li>Magma sorcery boost is <strong>15%</strong>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100.</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 11.11% (at 100 Discovery).</li> 
 <li>At equal Fai/Int stat spread,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Prince of Death's Staff" href="/Prince+of+Death's+Staff" target="">Prince of Death's Staff</a>&nbsp;starts to outperform Gelmir Glintstone Staff once you hit 50 Int and 50 Fai. Prince of Death's Staff also pulls ahead when stat investment is skewed more heavily towards Fai or Int as long as that stat value is over 50. 
  <ul> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 40 Int/40 Fai 264</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 50 Int/50 Fai 285</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 60 Int/60 Fai 296</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 70 Int/70 Fai 307</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 75 Int/25 Fai 254</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 25 Int/75 Fai 254</li> 
   <li>+25 Sorcery Scaling at 80 Int/80 Fai 318</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Gelmir Glintstone Staff</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Gelmir Glintstone Staff Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Gelmir Glintstone Staff Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (1)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(1)" target="">Smithing Stone [1]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (2)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(2)" target="">Smithing Stone [2]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (3)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(3)" target="">Smithing Stone [3]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (4)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(4)" target="">Smithing Stone [4]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (5)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(5)" target="">Smithing Stone [5]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (6)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(6)" target="">Smithing Stone [6]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (7)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(7)" target="">Smithing Stone [7]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (8)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(8)" target="">Smithing Stone [8]</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone" href="/Ancient+Dragon+Smithing+Stone">Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone</a>.</p> 
<p>Sorcery Scaling for this staff takes equal scaling from both Int and Faith stats. The stats of the the character with the staff&nbsp;equipped at the time of posting the&nbsp;<span style="color: #00ffff;">Sor Scaling</span>&nbsp;is located in the&nbsp;(Int/Fai)&nbsp;to the right of the scaling amount. This will help to give a general idea of what staves are better at various Int and Faith levels until MAX is achieved.</p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>. <span style="color: #00ffff;">The Sorcery Scaling displayed on this table shows Minimum Requirement and Intelligence / Faith 80 as xx-yy.</span></p> 
